Lagos – Olga Diyachenko, wife of Super Eagles captain, John Mikel Obi, has charged the team to put the 2-0 loss to Croatia behind them and keep on fighting at the ongoing World Cup in Russia. Though, she admitted that it was painful seeing the Super Eagles lose their first match, the Russian stressed that Mikel was always a winner in her eyes and charged Nigeria to go for victory against Iceland on Friday. DAILY INDEPENDENT gathered that she is very optimistic and keeping trust in her husband to shine at the World Cup, as she believes the Super Eagles’ captain and his teammates will bounce back from Saturday’s loss to Croatia. Olga took to social media to console the team over the defeat, but enthused that they would bounce back, while also encouraging her husband to remain a winner, despite a disappointing start to the tournament. She wrote: “You win some, you lose some my love… you are always a winner in my eyes. Love you. Go Nigeria.” comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 